India’s Coal Output Drops, Misses August Target, India Coal Says

-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 
2011-09-30T09:13:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/india-s-coal-output-drops-misses-august-target-india-coal-says.html
India ’s coal output fell 15 percent
in August from a year earlier and was short of a government-set
target, India Coal Market Watch said.  The country produced 32.32 million metric tons, compared
with a target of 40.37 million, said the newsletter, published
by Kolkata-based online trading company Mjunction Services Ltd.  Coal India Ltd. produced 25.01 million tons, with Singareni
Collieries Co. and captive coal mines accounting for the rest,
according to the newsletter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in Singapore at 
 dinakar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
